		<!-- //.conTop -->
		<div class="conBottom">
			<div class="conBottomInner">
				<dl class="infoList tabList type2">
					<dt>Definition</dt>
					<dd>
						<p>
							The Delete and Remove functions are used to delete or remove items. The Remove function removes an item from the current screen, not from the source path.<br>The Delete function deletes an item from all paths in the TV.
						</p>
						<p class="padL18 marT18 col59">
							<strong>Example : </strong><br>
Delete – When uninstalling an app from the TV<br>
Remove – When removing an app from the Home list
						</p>
					</dd>
					<dt>Usage</dt>
					<dd>
						<ul class="indentList">
							<li>- The Delete and Remove functions should be performed after obtaining a user’s confirmation. Basic popup is recommended for confirmation.</li>
							<li>- It can or cannot indicate the progress status after the user confirmation.</li>
							<li>- After finishing the Delete and Remove progress, it should inform users of the results. Toast popup is recommended for completion.</li>
						</ul>
						<ul class="listStyle02">
							<li>
								<img src="../../../img/ui_strategy/navigation/delete_remove/1.png" alt="">
							</li>
						</ul>
					</dd>
				</dl>
				<dl class="tagDl">
					<dt>*Tags :</dt>
					<dd>
					<span class="tagItem" linkTag="dep9_2_1">Basic Popup</span>,
					<span class="tagItem" linkTag="dep9_2_2">Toast Popup</span>
					</dd>
				</dl>
